* [[:en:Beppu Onsen|Beppu Onsen]]: In addition to the city-operated {{ill|Takegawara Onsen|ja|竹瓦温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takegawara Onsen|qq=}} and {{ill|Kannawa mushiyu|ja|鉄輪むし湯|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kannawa mushiyu|qq=}}, there are hundreds of {{ill|Communal onsen|ja|共同温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Communal onsen|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 共同浴場}} in Beppu City run by local residents.
** {{ill|Beppu Hatto Onsen Dō|ja|別府八湯温泉道|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Beppu Hatto Onsen Dō|qq=}}: Visitors can try 88 different baths, including these communal ones and day-use baths at ryokan, aiming for recognition as a “Hot Spring Master.”

